# SclJet SQL scalar functions

Scalar functions inside expressions: `UPPER`/`LOWER` (ASCII case), `LENGTH` (character count of the
text form), `ABS`, and `COALESCE` (first non-null). They compose with arithmetic and appear both in the
projection and in `WHERE` (`WHERE LENGTH(name) > 3`, `WHERE UPPER(name) = 'BOB'`). A NULL argument gives
NULL (except COALESCE). Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the
same file (verified out-of-band); locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlNull, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "people", "CREATE TABLE people(id INTEGER, name TEXT, age INTEGER, nick TEXT)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("Ann"), SqlInteger(30L), SqlNull),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(25L), SqlText("Bobby")),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("CHARLIE"), SqlInteger(40L), SqlNull))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT id, UPPER(name) FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT id, LOWER(name) FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT id, LENGTH(name) FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT id, ABS(age - 30) FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT id, COALESCE(nick, name) FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM people WHERE LENGTH(name) > 3")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM people WHERE UPPER(name) = 'BOB'")
    show(db, "SELECT UPPER(name) FROM people WHERE age >= 30 ORDER BY id")
```
